Sonia Garcia-Ruiz

Bio

I am a Computer Scientist living in Cambridge (UK). My research currently focuses on using short-read transcriptomic data to understand RNA splicing changes in human disease, with a special focus in neurodegeneration. But, of course, I also love talking about cats, music and philosophy.
